The new beastlord lvl 64 pet does less melee damage then our air pet. When all the mage buffs (summoned items) are given to this pet his value moves that much ahead of beastlord pets. This pet mitigates damage better then the level 64 beastlord. <br>
<br>
The level 62 water pet does over 100dps if given all the mage summoned gear. That is including melee damage, procs, spell damage ect...The level 64 warder is very close to the mage 61 air pet but still inferior. The Mage epic pet can still out damage the lvl 64 warder if it can land procs on the mob. Epic pet also still tanks considerably better then the beastlord lvl 64 warder.<br>
<br>
So where exactly is the problem? Our air pet has more hps and tanks better then the lvl 64 warder and does more damage. It also cast a stun to further help it mitigate damage. The lvl 62 water pet has around the same hps at the level 64 warder, tanks a little bit worse and out does it by about 40dps. Where is the problem people?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Mages all around are blinded by their new toys and nuking for so much more, that we don't even care if beastlords do way more sustained damage than us, have slow, and some killer mana regen spells/AA. IMO, that's all that matters-- not how balanced we are, but how balanced we think we are.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Lol more nonsense. A well played mage can blow away a beastlord in sustained dps. lvl 64 warder and his owner can barely out damage the level lvl 62 mage water pet. Maybe people don't understand how much 100+ dps is. My water pet does 115 to 125dps in UP (that is including melee, procs, spell damage) alone. How can you even begin to say things like a beastlord can even compete with a mage in damage. They are not even close.<br>
<br>
Beastlords are like shaman. They have slow and that allows them to solo. However 95% of beastlords do not have there level 60 slow which is 50%. Also most beastlords are never going to see there level 65 slow. I almost never see beastlords soloing in PoP. Only like the 3 or 4 on my server that are lucky enough to have the level 60 slow spell. It is even more rare then torpor and sunstrike combined.<br>
<br>
Wezloc<br>
